rComments: Not a bad teacher at all; very interested in the topic and generally does a decent job of keeping lectures semi-interesting. Attendance/participation are important, and he tends to enjoy giving pop quizzes. Not a "hard" class by any measure (very easy midterm/final), but you need to show up.

discussion sections are supposed to make things more understandable, unfortunately most of the time his discussion sections were him asking questions and the rest of the room was silent. talk about the longest 50 minutes ever. i give him credit for trying though, and having to work with prof. loughran (yuck!)
